benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/invoices - Retrieve account invoices

covered: Valid Request scenarios TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC06, TC07 demonstrate successful retrieval across multiple parameter configurations
Empty Response TC08 covers scenario where the account has no invoices
Pagination TC16 addresses large datasets and pagination behavior
Query Parameters TC02–TC07, TC09, TC21–TC23, TC24, TC27 cover valid/invalid parameter combinations and edge cases
Authorization TC12 and TC13 validate missing and invalid authentication
Edge cases and resilience TC14, TC15, TC21–TC23, TC27, TC28 test error handling, input validation and data inconsistencies
Regression and backwards compatibility TC19 and TC20
Downstream resilience and concurrency TC17 and TC18
gaps: Rate Limiting: no explicit tests for throttling or 429 responses present
Caching Behavior: no tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control)
Internal server error: no explicit 500 error scenario testing server-side failures
Authorization: no explicit 403 Forbidden scenarios to cover insufficient permissions
Explicit pagination controls: no dedicated tests for page/size pagination
Date format validation: no tests for invalid date formats beyond injection/XSS scenarios
recommendations: Add rate limiting/throttling tests to verify handling of high traffic and 429 responses
Add caching header validation and tests for ETag/Cache-Control
Add explicit 500 Internal Server Error scenarios to cover server/db failures
Add 403 Forbidden tests to cover insufficient permissions
Add explicit pagination parameter tests (page, per_page) and boundary cases
Add tests for invalid date formats and more robust date validation
